On the nature of consciousness: "Consciousness is a biological phenomenon, not a supernatural one."
On the importance of neuroscience: "To understand the mind, we must understand the brain."
On the limitations of traditional philosophical methods: "We need to supplement traditional philosophical methods with empirical research from neuroscience."
On the role of emotions: "Emotions are not irrational; they are biologically grounded responses to the world."
On the relationship between morality and biology: "Moral judgments are not arbitrary; they are shaped by our evolutionary history and neural circuitry."
